# dm CLI — Cursor Rules

## Codebase Reference

At the start of every session, read `docs/codebase.md` before exploring or searching the codebase.
This file contains the tech stack, folder structure, data flow, entry points, and known technical debt.
Use it to orient yourself and avoid redundant exploration.

## Keeping codebase.md Up to Date

After completing a task that changes the project structure, update the affected section(s) of `docs/codebase.md`.

| Change type | Section to update |
|-------------|-------------------|
| New dependency added/removed in `go.mod` | **Tech Stack** |
| New file, package, or directory created/deleted | **Folder Structure** (tree + file counts) |
| New Cobra command or tool registered | **Entry Points** |
| New plugin toolkit `.ps1` added | **Entry Points** (toolkit table) |
| Architecture change (new data path, changed LLM flow, new dispatch) | **Data Flow** |
| Bug fixed, debt resolved, or new debt introduced | **TODO / Debito Tecnico** |
| Roadmap item completed or new item added | **TODO / Debito Tecnico** (roadmap table) |
| Test file added to a previously uncovered package | **TODO / Debito Tecnico** (coverage gaps) |

Do NOT update `docs/codebase.md` for:
- Cosmetic changes (formatting, comments, variable renames)
- Internal refactors that don't change the public API or structure
- Minor bug fixes within existing functions

Always update the "Aggiornato:" date at the top of `docs/codebase.md` when editing it.

## Code Conventions

- Go source lives in `internal/` (private) and `tools/` (built-in tools).
- PowerShell toolkits live in `plugins/` and follow the naming convention `<Domain>_Toolkit.ps1`.
- Every toolkit function must have a prefix matching the toolkit (e.g., `spo_*` for SharePoint).
- Use `slog.Debug`/`slog.Warn` for agent-internal logging, `fmt.Print*` + `ui.*` for user output.
- Run `go build ./...` and `go test ./...` after changes; fix any failures before committing.
- Consult `AGENTS.md` for detailed PowerShell toolkit construction rules and agent decision engine specs.
